  "suggestion": "Survival gates all downstream fitness. Keep organisms alive longer by reducing energy waste and improving harvesting — beauty and efficiency follow.; Survival (0.5) is the critical bottleneck. Organisms die around age 250-300 and survivors at age 500 have critically low energy (7-34), indicating energy depletion. Dead organisms (IDs 0,1,3) exhausted reserves too quickly. Root cause: energyConserve too low (organisms hemorrhage energy), resourceAttraction insufficient (poor harvesting). Beauty is strong (0.748) so form mechanics work; efficiency (0.359) fails because alive organisms can't sustain. Fix: aggressive energyConserve boost to stop depletion, increase resourceAttraction to feed organisms, reduce moveSpeed to lower energy burn.",
